      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): surface non_deliverable_terminal_turn with specific message instead of generic /new fallback",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #94176 — When a model turn ends with `terminalError=non_deliverable_terminal_turn`, the user now sees actionable guidance instead of the misleading generic `/new` fallback.\n\n## Problem\n\nBefore this fix, when the model stopped between tool calls without producing a reply:\n- User saw: \"⚠️ Something went wrong while processing your request. Please try again, or use /new to start a fresh session.\"\n- `/new` is the wrong remediation — it clears context unnecessarily when a simple retry would succeed\n- No diagnostic signal reached the user about what actually happened\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`terminalError` from `resolveAttemptTrajectoryTerminal()` was recorded in trajectory events but NOT included in `runResult.meta`, so the reply system never saw it. The empty `terminalErrorMessage` caused the lifecycle to emit `end` instead of `error`, and downstream the generic fallback was used.\n\n## Fix (5 files, +28 lines)\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `agent-runner-failure-copy.ts` | Add `NON_DELIVERABLE_TERMINAL_TURN_FAILURE_TEXT` |\n| `agent-lifecycle-terminal.ts` | Add `terminalError` to deferred metadata keys |\n| `attempt.ts` | Surface `terminalError` + `terminalStatus` in runResult |\n| `agent-runner-execution.ts` | Check terminalError in terminalErrorMessage + buildExternalRunFailureReply |\n| `followup-runner.ts` | Same terminalError check |\n\nThe new user-facing message:\n> ⚠️ The model stopped between tool calls without producing a reply. Please try the same message again — this usually resolves on retry. If it persists, use /new or a lighter model.",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94176-non_deliverable_terminal_turn",
